  "texts": [
    "The findings show that collective memory can be both spatially visualized and quantified, while revealing clear regional differentiation.",
    "Consequently, the study provides a sociologically grounded method for assessing urban spatial value that informs evaluations of urban resilience and cultural continuity.",
    "Urbanization is reshaping urban forms at an unprecedented pace.",
    "However, the prevailing governance paradigm-centered on efficiency, form, and capital-increasingly reveals risks in practice, such as spatial homogenization and placelessness, which in turn weaken residents' emotional attachment to the city and undermine public identity 1.",
    "The concept of collective memory was first introduced in 1925 by French sociologist Maurice Halbwachs 2."
